messages.content: You are tasked with creating a structured output from the provided user message.

- Full path:
  /printshops/{printShopID}/employees

- All HTTP methods acceptable: false

- HEAD: false
- POST: true
- OPTIONS: false
- TRACE: false
- GET: true
- PUT: true
- DELETE: false
- PATCH: false

Explanation:
- The addEmployee method is annotated with @RequestMapping(value = "/printshops/{printShopID}/employees", method = RequestMethod.POST), so POST is explicitly accepted at the path /printshops/{printShopID}/employees.
- The same controller also defines handlers for the identical path with RequestMethod.GET (getEmployees) and RequestMethod.PUT (editEmployee), so GET and PUT are explicitly accepted for this exact path as well.
- DELETE is implemented in this controller but is mapped to /printshops/{printShopID}/employees/{employeeID} (has an extra path segment), so DELETE does not apply to /printshops/{printShopID}/employees.
- There are no explicit mappings for HEAD, OPTIONS, TRACE, or PATCH in the code for this path; per the task instructions I did not assume any framework-provided implicit handling, so these methods are reported as not acceptable.
